      "justification": "If confirmed, this means the paper's primary theoretical contribution (the information bound) has limited practical diagnostic power without additional empirical work. The bound is mathematically true but epistemologically empty without an independently specified Z. This doesn't invalidate the paper's conclusions (which are conditional on the model), but it severely limits their applicability. The paper needs to either provide a method for constructing falsifiable Z or reframe the theorem as purely mathematical scaffolding."
    },
    {
      "finding": "The conditional independence assumption S ⟂ T | (G, Z) is presented as a 'modeling assumption' but is essentially the phenomenon being explained (correlated errors). The paper analyzes consequences of this assumption rather than providing evidence that it holds in real LLM systems.",
      "severity": "MAJOR-REVISION",
      "justification": "If confirmed, this means the theoretical results describe a possible failure regime rather than demonstrating that real LLMs are in this regime. The paper's conclusions about LLM limitations are conditional on this unverified assumption. This requires either empirical validation of the assumption or clearer framing that the results are hypothetical."
